          <fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Under the hypotheses of <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-ii-1.4.11" href="hodge-theory-ii-1.4.11.xml" number="1.4.11" />:

    
 <html:ol xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
      
 <html:li style="list-style-type: &quot;(i) &quot;">
        The initial terms of the hypercohomology spectral sequences
        <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[           {}_WE_1^{q,n-q}           = \mathrm {R}^nT(\operatorname {Gr}_W^qK)           \Rightarrow  \mathrm {R}^nT(K)         \tag{1}         ]]></fr:tex>
        <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[           {}_FE_1^{p,n-p}           = \mathrm {R}^nT(\operatorname {Gr}_F^pK)           \Rightarrow  \mathrm {R}^nT(K)         \tag{2}         ]]></fr:tex>
        
        are abutments of the hypercohomology spectral sequences of the filtered complexes <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Gr}_W^qK]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Gr}_F^pK]]></fr:tex>, with <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E_1]]></fr:tex> pages given by
        <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[           E_1^{p,q,n-p-q}           \coloneqq  \mathrm {R}^nT(\operatorname {Gr}_F^p\operatorname {Gr}_W^qK)           \Rightarrow  {}_WE_1^{q,n-q}           \qquad \text {for fixed }q         \tag{3}         ]]></fr:tex>
        <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[           E_1^{p,q,n-p-q}           \coloneqq  \mathrm {R}^nT(\operatorname {Gr}_F^p\operatorname {Gr}_W^qK)           \Rightarrow  {}_FE_1^{p,n-p}           \qquad \text {for fixed }p         \tag{4}         ]]></fr:tex>
      </html:li>


      
 <html:li style="list-style-type: &quot;(ii) &quot;">
        The filtration of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{}_WE_1^{p,n-p}]]></fr:tex>, abutting to the spectral sequence <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(3)]]></fr:tex>, is the filtration of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{}_WE_1^{p,n-p}(TK')]]></fr:tex> induced by the filtration <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[TK']]></fr:tex>.
      </html:li>


      
 <html:li style="list-style-type: &quot;(iii) &quot;">
        For the differentials of the complexes <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Gr}_W^n(T(K'))]]></fr:tex> to be strictly compatible with the filtration <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex>, it is necessary and sufficient that the hypercohomology spectral sequences <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(3)]]></fr:tex> degenerate on the <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E_1]]></fr:tex> page.
      </html:li>


      
 <html:li style="list-style-type: &quot;(iv) &quot;">
        The morphisms <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[d_1]]></fr:tex> of the spectral sequence <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(4)]]></fr:tex> are the initial terms of the degree-1 morphisms of the spectral sequences <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(3)]]></fr:tex> that abut to the morphisms <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[d_1]]></fr:tex> of the spectral sequence <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(1)]]></fr:tex>.
      </html:li>

    </html:ol></fr:p>
  
    
