      Claim (ii) is then trivial by the definition of the recurrent filtration <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex> (identical to the discrete filtrations by <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-ii-1.3.10" href="hodge-theory-ii-1.3.10.xml" taxon="Lemma" number="1.3.10" /> and (iii) of <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-ii-1.3.13" href="hodge-theory-ii-1.3.13.xml" taxon="Proposition" number="1.3.13" />), and claim (iii) follows from <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-ii-1.3.2" href="hodge-theory-ii-1.3.2.xml" taxon="Proposition" number="1.3.2" />.</fr:p>
